        <mxCell id="SbDRJDh3eLq2FMcqhdqS-33" value="Interface should have same methods across all three options. For guidance, it should have method for sending commands to the simulation, and a method for receiving the state from the simulation. Assume perfect output." style="html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="590" y="50" width="190" height="160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="SbDRJDh3eLq2FMcqhdqS-34" value="State is described by:&lt;br&gt;Continuous:&lt;br&gt;- Position&lt;br&gt;- Velocity&lt;br&gt;- Mass&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Discrete:&lt;br&gt;- Stage number" style="html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="100" y="60" width="120" height="140" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="SbDRJDh3eLq2FMcqhdqS-35" value="Consider the simulation to always be initiating the request for guidance. It calls the interface at a certain frequency, which calls the guidance function and requests output. Guidance provides and interface returns results.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In the case of KSP and Orbiter, a clock will query the simulation and guidance." style="html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="800" y="50" width="230" height="162.5" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
